**Overall Meaning:**

"Wherever the breath is held in a limb afflicted by disease, etc., by holding it indeed, the breath obtains that healing."

**Explanation:**

This verse from the Upanishads emphasizes the healing power of pranayama, suggesting that focusing the breath on specific parts of the body can alleviate ailments and promote well-being.

**Breakdown:**

* **"यत्र यत्र धृतो वायुरङ्गे":**  This indicates that the breath should be consciously directed to any part of the body that is affected by disease or discomfort.
* **"रोगादिदूषिते":** This clarifies that the affected area could be suffering from various ailments, including disease, pain, or discomfort. 
* **"धारणादेव मरुत":** This emphasizes that simply holding the breath (pranayama) at the affected area is enough to initiate healing.
* **"तत्तदारोग्यमश्नुते":** This states that through this focused breath practice, the affected limb or area will obtain healing and relief.

This verse suggests that pranayama is a powerful tool for promoting physical health and well-being. By consciously directing the breath to specific parts of the body, one can potentially alleviate ailments and restore balance to the system. 
